verses.roman:
ekaika śākhāte upaśākhā śata śata
yata upajila śākhā ke gaṇibe kata

synonyms: ekaika—each branch; śākhāte—in the branch; upaśākhā—subbranches; śata śata—hundreds and hundreds; yata—all; upajila—grew; śākhā—branches; ke—who; gaṇibe—can count; kata—how much.
translation: From each branch grew many hundreds of subbranches. No one can count how many branches thus grew.
